User: Thomas suggested we need a basic preprocessing pipeline for our RAG framework. Can you implement that?
Ruby: Certainly! I'll create a preprocessing pipeline using some popular Ruby gems. Here's a basic implementation:

```ruby
require 'pragmatic_tokenizer'
require 'stopwords'
require 'lemmatizer'

class PreprocessingPipeline
  def initialize
    @tokenizer = PragmaticTokenizer::Tokenizer.new
    @stop_words = Stopwords::Snowball::Filter.new("en")
    @lemmatizer = Lemmatizer.new
  end

  def process(text)
    tokens = tokenize(text)
    tokens = remove_stop_words(tokens)
    tokens = lemmatize(tokens)
    tokens.join(' ')
  end

  private

  def tokenize(text)
    @tokenizer.tokenize(text)
  end

  def remove_stop_words(tokens)
    @stop_words.filter(tokens)
  end

  def lemmatize(tokens)
    tokens.map { |token| @lemmatizer.lemma(token) }
  end
end
```

This pipeline tokenizes the input text, removes stop words, and lemmatizes the remaining tokens. We can easily extend this class to include additional preprocessing steps as needed. Shall I explain any part of the code in more detail or move on to implementing the next component Thomas suggested?

